Flow Ficoll fluid slowly from the bottom of the tube (Fig.

                            8.1c
                          ).

Discard by aspirating the fluid overlaying the gradient interface (serum) leaving at least 5 ml of it over the leukocyte ring (Fig.

                            8.1d
                          ).

After resting, cells are directly stimulated with each of the candidate peptide (plus control) at the final concentration of 1 μM peptide or left unstimulated (DMSO solution only; negative control) (Fig.

                            8.2b
                          ).

Cell harvesting takes place afterwards by transferring cells from wells into 2 ml collection tube and centrifuging cells for 5 min at 1,500 rpm at room temperature (Fig.

                            8.2c
                          ).
